    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Vehicle Functions</title>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Cruise Control</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Road Speed Governing</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>PTO Governing</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Progressive Shifting</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Top Engine Speed Limiting</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>Since the PEEC control system is electronically programmable, there are several values that may be
            different from vehicle to vehicle per the owner specifications. These may include: maximum cruise speed,
            maximum road speed, maximum PTO speed, and shift schedules.
        </para>
        <para>For cruise control operation, refer to the Operator Manual.</para>
    </svcproc>
